      "name": "Yield force QoI validation — non-cannulated construct",
      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force was compared against experimental data drawn from a prior cannulated-screw ASTM F1717 fatigue characterization study (Berjano et al., 2014), which employed a comparable 7.5 mm outer-diameter titanium alloy pedicle screw construct under cyclic loading at 5 Hz. Yield force estimates were extracted from the load-displacement envelope reported in that study. The percentage difference between FEA prediction and the Berjano reference value was 7.3%, within the declared <10% bound. This corroborates the FEA framework's ability to capture peak load response.",
