      "rationale": "A second analyst at DePuy Synthes independently executed the model from the archived APDL input deck. Stiffness deviation 0.3%, yield force deviation 0.6%, force at 40 mm deviation 0.4%. All within 1% tolerance. Use error factor satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified by material characterization data; contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface kinematics; geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated from tensile coupon data (n=5 coupons, R²=0.997). UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic (E=1.1 GPa, ν=0.4) consistent with published ASTM F1717 test block properties. Augmented Lagrangian contact with frictional coefficient μ=0.2 at all metal-on-metal interfaces. Large-deflection formulation active throughout loading. Model form judged adequate for the QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and geometric inputs traceable to measured data or published standards; sensitivity analysis quantifies influence of uncertain inputs on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Screw geometry derived from manufacturer CAD (DePuy Synthes Expedium 5.5 rod system). Material properties sourced from lot-specific certificate of conformance and supplemental coupon testing. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for E (±10%), yield stress (±5%), and friction coefficient (±50%); maximum QoI sensitivity 4.2% for yield force to friction variation. Input uncertainty propagated into uval."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 experimental specimens from same lot; inter-laboratory reproducibility confirmed; specimen geometry verified by CMM.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from the same manufacturing lot tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). CMM verification confirmed screw outer diameter within ±0.02 mm of nominal. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness 3.1%, yield force 4.7%. Sample representativeness judged adequate."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple loading rates and angular offsets evaluated experimentally to characterize condition sensitivity; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) controlled and recorded.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single crosshead speed (5 mm/min) and single angular offset (5°) per ASTM F1717. No variation in loading rate or offset angle was explored experimentally. Laboratory temperature maintained at 23 ± 2°C. The single-condition limitation reduces confidence in model generalizability across the full COU envelope. This factor is assessed below required level and is flagged as a known limitation in the credibility argument."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading protocol match experimental setup to within documented tolerances; fixture compliance accounted for.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry: fixed inferior block, 5° anterior angulation, displacement-controlled superior loading. Fixture compliance measured at 0.08 mm/kN and incorporated as a spring element in the model. Angular alignment verified against laboratory fixture drawings. Equivalency confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized error metric E/uval computed for all three QoIs; all values < 1.96; percentage differences < 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval: stiffness 1.41, yield force — computed against primary experimental dataset 1.63, force at 40 mm 1.18. All three within 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences: stiffness 6.8%, yield force 7.3%, force at 40 mm 5.2%. All within 10% bound. Output comparison factor satisfied at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes of interest and are the same quantities reported in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the biological fusion mass. Yield force corresponds to the onset of permanent deformation that may accelerate fatigue failure. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are explicitly listed in the 510(k) submission performance testing section and map directly to the identified clinical risk of implant fracture leading to revision surgery."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
